(thirdQuint)Comparing Imaginal Exposure and Imagery Rescripting in Treatment of Posttraumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD).

 The main objectives of this study are: 1.

 To assess the relative efficacy of the two procedures in inpatient treatment for PTSD 2.

 To assess whether the predominant emotions in the traumatic memories moderate the outcome of the different procedures 3.

 To assess whether theory-derived constructs mediate outcome and whether the mediating relationships are different in the two treatments 4.

 To provide a theoretical account of the two models 5.

 To psychometrically evaluate 3 new measures.

